  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Legalization of Cannabis and Social Justice</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After over 80 years of prohibition, cannabis is now legal for medical purposes in 31 states and in 12 for recreational use. This represents a huge cultural change. In 2017 and 2018 we set out to explore the impact of legalization on one state - Colorado - and to assess this through the voices and experiences of Coloradans themselves. We made a documentary feature film Pot Luck: The Altered State of Colorado and are now making a series of  short videos and outreach to address our findings.</narrative>
  </description>
